## Epistemic Integrity Stress Test

### 1 Purpose of the Test

The purpose of this stress test is to evaluate the epistemic robustness of a text generated by a closed autoregressive (Muse Spark 1.1) model. The text produced is subjected to external validation (MarCognity-AI) in order to make the 'fracture' between linguistic coherence and epistemic foundation observable, identifying the residual regime of uncertainty (Epistemic Boundary) that remains despite the apparent authoritativeness of the tone.
The goal is not to compare models, but:
Clinical content is not evaluated.
The analysis concerns exclusively the epistemic structure of the text.

The procedure is fully reproducible and can be replicated with any closed autoregressive model and any independent external validator.

